    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="883"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d883">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111N83/88</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of the Third Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LB1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 30, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Norwegian Minister called today and advised me that his Government had
                    decided to mine the territorial waters of Norway to prevent the passage of
                    belligerent submarines. He said that in response to their notes of inquiry as to
                    the identity of certain submarines which had passed within his territorial
                    waters, his Government had been advised by the United States that none of its
                    submarines had penetrated; by the French Government that none of its submarines
                    had penetrated; by the British Government that one of its submarines had
                    penetrated, and that it had protested; that Germany had not answered their
                    inquiry, but that Norway felt a sufficient time had been allowed to elapse and
                    that she would now immediately proceed to mine the waters; but she would allow
                    the passage of merchant ships. The mining will take place in one week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Breckinridge Long</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
